Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette(?) bowl; interior glazed with added red band lined in white near lip; exterior: black line at top of rim; verticals in frieze, one of them, at left, set apart; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.828)
